## 🗄️ SQL Analysis — 10 Business Questions

| # | Business Question | SQL Technique |
|---|-------------------|---------------|
| 01 | Average daily return per stock | `AVG(daily_return) GROUP BY stock_name` |
| 02 | Most volatile stock | `STDEV(daily_return) GROUP BY stock_name` |
| 03 | Total return per stock | `SUM(daily_return) ORDER BY Total_Return DESC` |
| 04 | Highest average return month | `TOP 1 + ORDER BY highest_avg_return DESC` |
| 05 | Yearly average price trend | `AVG(close) GROUP BY year` |
| 06 | Stock with highest trading volume | `MAX(volume) GROUP BY stock_name` |
| 07 | Top 5 worst return days | `TOP 5 ORDER BY daily_return ASC` |
| 08 | Stock performance comparison | `AVG + STDEV GROUP BY stock_name` |
| 09 | Seasonal return trends | `SUM(daily_return) GROUP BY month` |
| 10 | Best stock for long-term (CTE) | `CTE: Initial vs Current Price → Total Return %` |

### Sample Query — Long-Term Investment Analysis (CTE)

```sql
WITH StockBounds AS (
    SELECT stock_name,
           MIN(date) AS start_date,
           MAX(date) AS end_date
    FROM stock
    GROUP BY stock_name
)
SELECT sb.stock_name,
       s_start.[close]  AS Initial_Price,
       s_end.[close]    AS Current_Price,
       ((s_end.[close] - s_start.[close]) / s_start.[close]) * 100 AS Total_Return_Percent
FROM StockBounds sb
JOIN stock s_start ON sb.stock_name = s_start.stock_name AND sb.start_date = s_start.date
JOIN stock s_end   ON sb.stock_name = s_end.stock_name   AND sb.end_date   = s_end.date;
```

